content.description: Crawl into the pit, and sit start low with your hands matched on the horizontal rail. Make a few moves to gain the arete, and climb to the top.
content.location: The overhanging boulder facing the river at the very bottom of the talus field.

content.description: This problem climbs a beautiful arete and overhanging face. Sit start low and climb the arete.
content.protection: Two pads. One for the hole, one for the landing.
content.location: The overhanging boulder facing the river at the very bottom of the talus field.

content.description:
Stand start. Reach up and find whatever works. Throw a right heal and surmount the bulge. The feature is beautiful, but the climbing is physical. 

  Leave the start up to your own ethics. Either establish a food on the "cheater" block supporting this boulder, or stand start and power through. Both are fun.
content.protection: Make sure that you have a spotter, so that you do not roll backward into the pit.
content.location: The suspended boulder facing the river at the very bottom of the talus field.

content.description:
This talus field is full of boulders!  

  The majority of them are two small to bother bouldering; however, there are a few diamonds in the rough.
